    "authority": "backend refactor review + R1 characterization gate; maintainer endorsed 2026-07-22",
    "diagnosis": "Canonical macOS UI RTF fell 1.04-1.15 (2026-07-16) to 0.88-0.93 (2026-07-20) to 0.69-0.81 (2026-07-22) while interleaved A/B/A CLI benches across the Phase 4 cutover (9a8da874 vs 610125b7 vs HEAD) stayed flat at 1.02-1.17. The engine in the app/XPC topology is submission-starved: ~25% CPU vs ~91% in CLI, zero lossless-channel producer suspensions, normal thread priorities, command buffers executing fast with ~83% of the buffer timeline submission-side idle (Metal System Trace, summarized then discarded). Working mechanism: per-frame cross-actor suspension points pay scheduler latency under foreground load, compounded by per-chunk v9 telemetry publication.",
    "evidence": [
      "macos-engine-20260722-210927-3553c1b1",
      "macos-xcui-benchmark-20260722-211254-273bd16d",
      "macos-xcui-benchmark-20260722-213731-c47b0d27",
      "macos-xcui-benchmark-20260716-181853-b4c2e299",
      "macos-xcui-benchmark-20260720-172920-591696d1"
    ],
    "changes": [
      "Phase 7 rescoped from raw chunk/preview RTF experiments to the delivery-pipeline pacing fix: coalesce per-frame actor hops, move v9 per-chunk publication off the generation path, and evaluate larger macOS chunk schedules; secret-sauce first-preview latency and trim/unload safety must not regress.",
      "Promotion characterization matrices must include at least one UI/app-XPC-context cell (promotedMatrixRequiresUIContextCell).",
      "Phase 14 mechanical retirement is pulled forward: scheduled immediately after the phase 7-9 block, before phases 10-13, so quality/long-form work builds on one topology."
    ]
